ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the practicability of our proposed strategy, actual samples came from laboratory tap water and on-campus lake water were chosen, and both were filtered before use. The original solutions were tested for the absence of Cr(VI) and Hg(II), so they were used as solvents and the recoveries were measured by the standard addition method. In the linear range, the recoveries of CDs for Cr(VI) are in 96.8%–103.3 % range (Table 1
                        ), and those for Hg(II) are in the range of 96.3%–100.5 % (Table 2
                        ), with RSD below 3 %. The above results demonstrate the high accuracy and feasibility of this protocol for the determination of Cr(VI) and Hg(II) in practical applications.
